<subSubSection id="DD9038D78E5B16F8433E307C81D6A646" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="4CA8AA2DB623F181B56B4D075A8B5AE0" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175">Diagnosis</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A7E7561B39FBFFD3DD769A41EC517DE6" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175">
Easily distinguished from more common 
<taxonomicName id="05A037B486A2936B3F9EE351B17D1C76" genus="H." lsidName="H. ferruginea" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175" rank="species" species="ferruginea">H. ferruginea</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="29DBC1E7A2A463929B3497E0726D3C93" originalValue="FallÃ©n">Fallen</normalizedToken>
by smaller body size and short feathering of the arista (Fig. 11, see also 
<bibRefCitation id="AA5DA4F6184562A412D9535138A0D95E" author="Kerppola, S." journalOrPublisher="Sahlbergia" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175" pagination="2 - 4" title="Hammerschmidtiaingrica Stackelberg, 1952 - Inkerinmahlanen Suomesta (Diptera, Syrphidae)" volume="17" year="2011">Kerppola (2011)</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 2-4).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="81777F1B9F8CAED91E316F65D8E208C5" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="E9E55C2A5DF228220A4A6263620CB23D" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph id="378D0D4FEC299A5FB5F597E0B3CFD3D8" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175">
Palaearctic. Few specimens are known from Finland and Leningrad province of Russia (
<bibRefCitation id="7727BC663C509B1817EAC3FE16F273EB" author="Kerppola, S." journalOrPublisher="Sahlbergia" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175" pagination="2 - 4" title="Hammerschmidtiaingrica Stackelberg, 1952 - Inkerinmahlanen Suomesta (Diptera, Syrphidae)" volume="17" year="2011">Kerppola 2011</bibRefCitation>
). In East Russia, recorded from the republic of Tyva to Primorje region (
<bibRefCitation id="707C8A4F09AEF22156D8559C15810128" author="Krivosheina, M. G." journalOrPublisher="Entomological Review" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175" pagination="361 - 367" title="A review of flower-flies of the genus Hammerschmidtia of Russia, with description of larva of H. ingrica (Diptera, Syrphidae)" volume="83" year="2003">Krivosheina 2003</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0383B63EFC8FA66842C41C00F58D2967" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175" type="ecology">
<paragraph id="3D4C72FEAF2B23FD2CC3E4F2A37F3C29" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175">Ecology</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C1C0CF2200A1304A5A06184818FD6DCB" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175">
Saproxylic species, associated with deciduous trees (
<bibRefCitation id="67375531630CA1868F3495ED8D6D9070" author="Krivosheina, M. G." journalOrPublisher="Entomological Review" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175" pagination="361 - 367" title="A review of flower-flies of the genus Hammerschmidtia of Russia, with description of larva of H. ingrica (Diptera, Syrphidae)" volume="83" year="2003">Krivosheina 2003</bibRefCitation>
). This fly was collected from a wind-broken aspen, colonised by 7 species of macrofungi Table 1.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="20E348C511A80E5171215B58FCFD1799" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175" type="conservation">
